title: Railer gymnasts second at state
text: Railer gymnasts second at state Comment Posted Oct. 24, 2015 at 6:46 PM Updated Oct 24, 2015 at 6:46 PM Posted Oct. 24, 2015 at 6:46 PM Newton, Kan. By Mark Schnabel Newton Kansan The Newton High School gymnastics team ended the season with a second-place finish Saturday at the KSHSAA state championships at Ravenscroft Gym. Olathe East won the meet at 109.15, followed by Newton at 106.525 and Shawnee Mission Northwest at 101.325. There were eight teams in competition. Carlye Anderson of Newton won the state title in the uneven parallel bars at 8.85. Kailey Naysmith claimed five medals, tying for second in the balance beam at 9.25. Naysmith was third in all-around at 36.375. Kaylee Anderson was sixth in all-around at 34.575 and claimed two other medals. More details will be in Tuesday's Kansan and at thekansan.com .
